        <p><span class="dropcap">B</span>efore a child grips a pencil, she fills a scoop. Before she counts, she sorts. Before she can name a feeling, she squeezes a ball of dough until she feels calm again. Sensory Play is the toolkit for that early, hands-first learning: maple trays sized for the Flisat, dual-sided tracing inserts, scented therapy dough, and sand trays for the morning-meeting reset. It needs no batteries and no instructions, only texture, attention, and unhurried time.</p>
